01158     rxData.m_pvt.nrAdrObsAvailable = 0;
01159     rxData.m_pvt.nrAdrObsUsed = 0;
01160     rxData.m_pvt.nrAdrObsRejected = 0;
01161 
01162     // Check for cycle slips.
01163     rxData.CheckForCycleSlips_UsingPhaseRatePrediction( GNSS_CYCLESLIP_THREADHOLD );
01164 
01165     nrUsableAdr = 0;    
01166     for( i = 0; i < rxData.m_nrValidObs; i++ )
01167     {
01168       if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isActive )
01169       {
01170         if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].system == GNSS_GPS && rxData.m_ObsArray[i].freqType == GNSS_GPSL1 )
01171         {
01172           if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].satellite.elevation < rxData.m_elevationMask )              
01173             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveElevationMask = 0;
01174           else
01175             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveElevationMask = 1;
01176 
01177           if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].cno < rxData.m_cnoMask )
01178             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveCNoMask = 0;
01179           else
01180             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveCNoMask = 1;
01181

01183             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveLockTimeMask = 0;
01184           else
01185             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveLockTimeMask = 1;
01186 
01187           isGood = 
01188             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isCodeLocked         &
01189             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPhaseLocked        &
01190             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isParityValid        & // if not, there is a half cycle amibiguity.
01191             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrValid           &
01192             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveElevationMask &
01193             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveCNoMask       &
01194             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveLockTimeMask  &
01195             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotUserRejected    &

01201             nrUsableAdr++;            
01202           }
01203           else
01204           {
01205             rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrUsedInSolution = 0;
01206           }
01207         }
01208       }
01209     }
01210     rxData.m_pvt.nrAdrObsAvailable = nrUsableAdr;
01211     return true;

01215   bool GNSS_Estimator::DetermineDesignMatrixForThePositionSolution_GPSL1( 
01216     GNSS_RxData &rxData,      //!< The receiver data.
01217     const unsigned nrRowsInH, //!< The number of valid rows in H.
01218     Matrix &H                 //!< The position & rx clock design matrix [n x 4].
01219     )
01220   {

01222     unsigned j = 0;

01224     // Check the dimension of H.
01225     if( H.GetNrRows() != nrRowsInH || H.GetNrCols() != 4 )
01226     {
01227       if( !H.Resize( nrRowsInH, 4 ) )

01243             NAVIGATION_ComputeDerivativesOf_Range_WithRespectToLatitudeLongitudeHeight(

01437   bool GNSS_Estimator::DeterminePseudorangeMisclosures_GPSL1( 
01438     GNSS_RxData *rxData,     //!< The pointer to the receiver data.    
01439     GNSS_RxData *rxBaseData, //!< The pointer to the reference receiver data. NULL if not available.    
01440     const unsigned n,        //!< The number of misclosures.
01441     Matrix &w                //!< The pseudorange misclosure vector [n x 1].
01442     )
01443   {
01444     unsigned i = 0;
01445     unsigned j = 0;
01446     int k = 0;
01447     double psr_base = 0;
01448     double range_base = 0;
01449     double psr_measured = 0;
01450     double psr_computed = 0;
01451 
01452     // Check the dimension of w.
01453     if( w.GetNrRows() != n || w.GetNrCols() != 1 )
01454     {
01455       if( !w.Resize( n, 1 ) )
01456         return false;
01457     }
01458 
01459     for( i = 0; i < rxData->m_nrValidObs; i++ )
01460     {
01461       if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isActive )
01462       {
01463         if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system == GNSS_GPS && rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType == GNSS_GPSL1 )
01464         {
01465           // allows compute the misclosure value (regardless of whether it is used in solution
01466           psr_measured = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].psr;
01467 
01468           // Add the satellite clock correction.
01469           psr_measured += rxData->m_ObsArray[i].satellite.clk;
01470 
01471           // Compensate for the ionospheric delay if indicated.
01472           // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01473           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection )
01474           {
01475             // Compensate for the ionospheric delay
01476             psr_measured -= rxData->m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcIono;
01477           }
01478 
01479           // Compensate for the tropospheric delay if indicated.
01480           // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01481           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.useTropoCorrection )
01482           {
01483             // Compensate for the tropospheric delay
01484             psr_measured -= rxData->m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoDry;
01485             psr_measured -= rxData->m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoWet;
01486           }
01487 
01488           range_base = 0;
01489           if( rxBaseData != NULL )
01490           {    
01491             if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialPsrAvailable )
01492             {
01493               k = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_differential;
01494               if( k != -1 )
01495               {
01496                 psr_base  = rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].psr;
01497                 psr_base += rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].satellite.clk;
01498 
01499                 // Compensate for the ionospheric delay if indicated.
01500                 // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01501                 if( rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection )
01502                 {
01503                   // Compensate for the ionospheric delay
01504                   psr_base -= rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].corrections.prcIono;
01505                 }
01506 
01507                 // Compensate for the tropospheric delay if indicated.
01508                 // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01509                 if( rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].flags.useTropoCorrection )
01510                 {
01511                   // Compensate for the tropospheric delay
01512                   psr_base -= rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].corrections.prcTropoDry;
01513                   psr_base -= rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].corrections.prcTropoWet;
01514                 }                  
01515 
01516                 range_base = rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].range;
01517 
01518                 // Compute the differential pseudorange.
01519                 psr_measured -= psr_base;
01520               }
01521             }
01522           }
01523 
01524           // Calculate the computed pseudorange = geometric range + clock offset (m)
01525           // The range value and the clock offset must be determined beforehand.
01526           // If differential, range_base != 0, it is the computed psuedorange difference.
01527           psr_computed = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].range - range_base + rxData->m_pvt.clockOffset;
01528 
01529           // The misclosure is the corrected measured value minus the computed valid.
01530           rxData->m_ObsArray[i].psr_misclosure = psr_measured - psr_computed;            
01531 
01532           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPsrUsedInSolution )
01533           {
01534             // Sanity index check.
01535             if( j >= n )
01536               return false;
01537 
01538             w[j] = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].psr_misclosure;
01539             j++;
01540           }
01541         }
01542         else
01543         {
01544           rxData->m_ObsArray[i].psr_misclosure = 0.0;            
01545         }
01546       }
01547     }
01548 
01549     // Deal with constraints.
01550     if( rxData->m_pvt.isPositionConstrained )
01551     {
01552       if( j + 3 > n )
01553         return false;
01554 
01555       double N;
01556       double M;
01557       double diff;
01558 
01559       GEODESY_ComputePrimeVerticalRadiusOfCurvature(
01560         GEODESY_REFERENCE_ELLIPSE_WGS84,
01561         rxData->m_prev_pvt.latitude,
01562         &N );
01563       GEODESY_ComputeMeridianRadiusOfCurvature( 
01564         GEODESY_REFERENCE_ELLIPSE_WGS84,
01565         rxData->m_prev_pvt.latitude,
01566         &M );
01567             
01568       diff = (rxData->m_prev_pvt.latitude - rxData->m_pvt.latitude);
01569       diff *= ( M + rxData->m_prev_pvt.height ); // convert to meters.
01570       w[j] = diff;
01571       j++;
01572       diff = (rxData->m_prev_pvt.longitude - rxData->m_pvt.longitude );
01573       diff *= (N + rxData->m_prev_pvt.height)*cos(rxData->m_prev_pvt.latitude); // convert to meters.
01574       w[j] = diff;
01575       j++;
01576       w[j] = rxData->m_prev_pvt.height - rxData->m_pvt.height;
01577       j++;      
01578     }
01579     else if( rxData->m_pvt.isHeightConstrained )
01580     {
01581       if( j + 1 > n )
01582         return false;
01583             
01584       w[j] = rxData->m_prev_pvt.height - rxData->m_pvt.height;
01585       j++;
01586     }
01587 
01588 
01589     return true;
01590   }

01736         if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system == GNSS_GPS && rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType == GNSS_GPSL1 )
01737         {
01738           // allows computation of the misclosure value (regardless of whether it is used in solution
01739           adr_measured = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].adr * GPS_WAVELENGTHL1;
01740 
01741           // Add the satellite clock correction.
01742           adr_measured += rxData->m_ObsArray[i].satellite.clk;
01743 
01744           // Compensate for the ionospheric delay if indicated.
01745           // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01746           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection )
01747           {
01748             // Compensate for the ionospheric delay
01749             adr_measured += rxData->m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcIono;
01750           }
01751 
01752           // Compensate for the tropospheric delay if indicated.
01753           // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01754           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.useTropoCorrection )
01755           {
01756             // Compensate for the tropospheric delay
01757             adr_measured -= rxData->m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoDry;
01758             adr_measured -= rxData->m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoWet;
01759           }
01760 
01761           range_base = 0;
01762           if( rxBaseData != NULL )
01763           {    
01764             if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialAdrAvailable )
01765             {
01766               k = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_differential;
01767               if( k != -1 )
01768               {
01769                 adr_base  = rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].adr * GPS_WAVELENGTHL1;
01770                 adr_base += rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].satellite.clk;
01771                 
01772                 // Compensate for the ionospheric delay if indicated.
01773                 // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01774                 if( rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection )
01775                 {
01776                   // Compensate for the ionospheric delay
01777                   adr_base += rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].corrections.prcIono;
01778                 }
01779 
01780                 // Compensate for the tropospheric delay if indicated.
01781                 // The corrections must be determined beforehand.
01782                 if( rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].flags.useTropoCorrection )
01783                 {
01784                   // Compensate for the tropospheric delay
01785                   adr_base -= rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].corrections.prcTropoDry;
01786                   adr_base -= rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].corrections.prcTropoWet;
01787                 }                  
01788 
01789                 range_base = rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[k].range;
01790 
01791                 // Compute the differential adr.
01792                 adr_measured -= adr_base;
01793               }
01794             }
01795           }
01796 
01797           // Calculate the computed adr = geometric range + clock offset (m)
01798           // The range value and the clock offset must be determined beforehand.
01799           // If differential, range_base != 0, and the ambiguity is the single differnce ambiguity [m].
01800           adr_computed = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].range - range_base;
01801           adr_computed += rxData->m_pvt.clockOffset;          
01802           adr_computed += rxData->m_ObsArray[i].ambiguity; 
01803 
01804           // The misclosure is the corrected measured value minus the computed valid.
01805           rxData->m_ObsArray[i].adr_misclosure = adr_measured - adr_computed;            
01806 
01807           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrUsedInSolution )
01808           {
01809             // Sanity index check.
01810             if( j >= n )
01811               return false;
01812 
01813             w[j] = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].adr_misclosure;
01814             j++;
01815           }
01816         }
01817         else
01818         {
01819           rxData->m_ObsArray[i].adr_misclosure = 0.0;            
01820         }
01821       }
01822     }
01823     return true;
01824   }

02157   /// \brief    Perform the Global Internal Reliability Test, followed by a 
02158   ///           search using local testing for a single measurement fault if 
02159   ///           the global test fails.
02160   ///
02161   /// The Global Internal Reliability Test: \n
02162   /// The aposteriori variance factor is computed and compared to the value 
02163   /// generated using Chi^2 lookup table. The aposerteriori variance factor 
02164   /// indicates the following: \n
02165   /// if( apv ~= 1 ) \n
02166   ///   solution and observations are well modelled. \n
02167   /// if( apv < 1 ) \n
02168   ///   observation variance matrix is pessimistic. \n
02169   ///   (observations are better than what you said). \n
02170   /// if( apv > 1 ) \n
02171   ///   (1) The math model incorrect, (not likely) \n
02172   ///   (2) The weight matrix/observation variance matrix is optimistic 
02173   ///      (observations are worse than what you said). \n
02174   ///   (3) Their is a blunder in the observations that is skewing the normality 
02175   ///       of the solution, and a local test for blunder my be needed. \n
02176   ///
02177   bool GNSS_Estimator::PerformGlobalTestAndTestForMeasurementFaults( 
02178     GNSS_RxData &rxData,           //!< The receiver data object.
02179     bool testPsrOrDoppler,         //!< This indicates if the psr misclosures are checked, otherwise the Doppler misclosures are checked. 
02180     Matrix& H,                     //!< The design matrix, H,                           [n x u].
02181     Matrix& Ht,                    //!< The design matrix transposed, H,                [n x u].
02182     Matrix& W,                     //!< The observation weight matrix, W,               [n x n].
02183     Matrix& R,                     //!< The observation variance-covariance matrix, R,  [n x n].
02184     Matrix& r,                     //!< The observation residual vector,                [n x 1].
02185     Matrix& P,                     //!< The state variance-covariance matrix,           [u x u].
02186     const unsigned char n,         //!< The number of observations, n.
02187     const unsigned char u,         //!< The number of unknowns, u.
02188     double &avf,                   //!< The computed a-posteriori variance factor is returned.
02189     bool &isGlobalTestPassed,      //!< This indicates if the global test passed.    
02190     bool &hasRejectionOccurred,    //!< This indicates if a rejection occurred. Only one measurement is flagged.
02191     unsigned char &indexOfRejected //!< This is the index of the rejected observation.
02192     )
02193   {
02194     double v = n-u; // The degree of freedom.
02195 
02196     unsigned i = 0;
02197     unsigned j = 0; 
02198     unsigned indexvec[GNSS_RXDATA_NR_CHANNELS]; // An array with the indices measurements that are used in solution.
02199 
02200     double rv = 0;           // An unsigned standardized residual value.
02201     double largest_rv = 0.0; // The largest unsigned standardized residual value.    
02202     unsigned char indexOfLargest = 0; // The index of the largest standardized residual value.  
02203 
02204     double chiSquaredValue = 0;                     // The chi squared test value = look up table value / degrees of freedom.
02205     double chiSquared005[31] = GNSS_CHISQUARE_00_5; // The chi squared look up table for alpha = 0.005.
02206     
02207     // Initial output values.
02208     isGlobalTestPassed = false;
02209     hasRejectionOccurred = false;      
02210     
02211     Matrix Cr;             // The variance-covariance matrix of the residuals [n x n].
02212     Matrix rT;             // The residuals vector transposed,                [1 x n]
02213     Matrix r_standardized; // The standardized residuals,                     [n x 1].
02214     Matrix tmpM;
02215 
02216     PrintMatToDebug( "P", P );
02217 
02218     i = static_cast<unsigned>(v);
02219     if( i == 0 )
02220       return true; 
02221     
02222     rT = r;
02223     if( !rT.Inplace_Transpose() )
02224       return false;
02225 
02226     // Compute the a-posteriori variance factor.
02227     tmpM = rT * W * r;
02228     avf = tmpM[0] / v;
02229     
02230     // Determine the chi squared test statistic value.
02231     i = static_cast<unsigned>(v);
02232     if( i < 0 || i > 30 )
02233       return false;
02234     chiSquaredValue = chiSquared005[i];
02235     chiSquaredValue /= v;
02236     
02237     // Perform the Global Test.
02238     if( avf < chiSquaredValue )
02239     {
02240       // The Global test passes. No local test will be performed.
02241       isGlobalTestPassed = true;
02242       return true;
02243     }
02244 
02245     // Check that there is enough redudancy to remove outliers.
02246     i = static_cast<unsigned>(v);
02247     if( i <= 0 )
02248     {
02249       return true;
02250     }
02251 
02252     
02253     ////
02254     // Perform the local test.
02255 
02256     // Determine the indices of the observations that match the
02257     // values in the residuals vector.
02258     j = 0;
02259     for( i = 0; i < rxData.m_nrValidObs; i++ )
02260     {
02261       if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isActive )
02262       {
02263         if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].system == GNSS_GPS && rxData.m_ObsArray[i].freqType == GNSS_GPSL1 )
02264         {
02265           if( testPsrOrDoppler )
02266           {
02267             if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPsrUsedInSolution )
02268             {
02269               indexvec[j] = i;
02270               j++;
02271             }
02272           }
02273           else
02274           {
02275             if( rxData.m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDopplerUsedInSolution )
02276             {
02277               indexvec[j] = i;
02278               j++;
02279             }
02280           }
02281         }        
02282       }
02283     }
02284     
02285     
02286     // Compute the variance-covariance of the residuals.
02287     Cr = R - H * P * Ht;
02288 
02289     PrintMatToDebug( "Cr", Cr );
02290 
02291 
02292     // Check the diagonal of Cr for zero and negative values, an error condition.
02293     for( i = 0; i < Cr.GetNrRows(); i++ )
02294     {
02295       if( Cr[i][i] <= 0.0 )
02296       {
02297         return false;
02298       }
02299     }
02300 
02301     
02302     if( !r_standardized.Resize( Cr.GetNrRows(), 1) )
02303       return false;
02304 
02305     // Compute the standardized residuals, r(i) /= Cr(i,i).
02306     // Determine the largest standardized residual value.
02307     for( i = 0; i < Cr.GetNrRows(); i++ )
02308     {
02309       r_standardized[i] = r[i] / sqrt( Cr[i][i] );
02310 
02311       rv = fabs( r_standardized[i] );
02312 
02313       // don't allow the position constraint to be rejected.
02314       if( rxData.m_pvt.isPositionConstrained )
02315       {
02316         if( i >= Cr.GetNrRows() -3 )
02317           continue;
02318       }
02319 
02320       if( rv > largest_rv )
02321       {
02322         largest_rv = rv;
02323         indexOfLargest = i; // This is the index into r.
02324       }
02325     }
02326     indexOfLargest = indexvec[indexOfLargest]; // This is the index into the observation array.
02327 
02328     // sanity index check
02329     if( indexOfLargest >= rxData.m_nrValidObs )
02330       return false;
02331 
02332     PrintMatToDebug( "r", r );
02333     PrintMatToDebug( "r_standardized", r_standardized );
02334     
02335     // In reliability testing, alpha = 0.005, n_(1-alpha/2) = 4.57
02336     if( largest_rv > 4.57 ) // reject only clear blunders
02337     {
02338       // An observation will be rejected.
02339       hasRejectionOccurred = true;      
02340 
02341       if( testPsrOrDoppler ) // true is pseudorange
02342         rxData.m_ObsArray[indexOfLargest].flags.isNotPsrRejected = 0;
02343       else
02344         rxData.m_ObsArray[indexOfLargest].flags.isNotDopplerRejected = 0;      
02345     }
02346 
02347     return true;
02348   }

02353     Matrix &T         //!< The transition matrix [8 x 8].
02354     )
02355   {
02356     const double betaVn       = 1.0/m_KF.alphaVn;       // The Gauss Markov beta for northing velocity [1/s].
02357     const double betaVe       = 1.0/m_KF.alphaVe;       // The Gauss Markov beta for easting velocity [1/s].
02358     const double betaVup      = 1.0/m_KF.alphaVup;      // The Gauss Markov beta for up velocity [1/s].
02359     const double betaClkDrift = 1.0/m_KF.alphaClkDrift; // The Gauss Markov beta for the clock drift [1/s].
02360 
02361     double eVn = 0;
02362     double eVe = 0;
02363     double eVup = 0;
02364     double eClkDrift = 0;
02365 
02366     
02367     if( T.GetNrRows() != 8 || T.GetNrCols() != 8 )
02368     {
02369       if( !T.Resize(8,8) )
02370         return false;
02371     }    
02372     
02373     eVn  = exp( -betaVn  * dT );
02374     eVe  = exp( -betaVe  * dT );
02375     eVup = exp( -betaVup * dT );
02376 
02377     eClkDrift = exp( -betaClkDrift * dT );
02378 
02379     T.Zero();
02380     
02381     T[0][0] = 1.0;
02382     T[0][3] = (1.0 - eVn) / betaVn;
02383 
02384     T[1][1] = 1.0;
02385     T[1][4] = (1.0 - eVe) / betaVe;
02386 
02387     T[2][2] = 1.0;
02388     T[2][5] = (1.0 - eVup) / betaVup;
02389     
02390     T[3][3] = eVn;
02391     T[4][4] = eVe;
02392     T[5][5] = eVup;
02393 
02394     T[6][6] = 1.0;
02395     T[6][7] = (1.0 - eClkDrift) / betaClkDrift;
02396 
02397     T[7][7] = eClkDrift;
02398 
02399     return true;
02400   }

02448   bool GNSS_Estimator::ComputeProcessNoiseMatrix_8StatePVGM(
02449     const double dT,  //!< The change in time since the last update [s].
02450     Matrix &Q         //!< The process noise matrix [8 x 8].
02451     )
02452   {
02453     const double betaVn       = 1.0/m_KF.alphaVn;       // The Gauss Markov beta for northing velocity [1/s].
02454     const double betaVe       = 1.0/m_KF.alphaVe;       // The Gauss Markov beta for easting velocity [1/s].
02455     const double betaVup      = 1.0/m_KF.alphaVup;      // The Gauss Markov beta for up velocity [1/s].
02456     const double betaClkDrift = 1.0/m_KF.alphaClkDrift; // The Gauss Markov beta for the clock drift [1/s].
02457 
02458     const double qVn       = 2 * m_KF.sigmaVn  * m_KF.sigmaVn  * betaVn;  // The process noise value for northing velocity.
02459     const double qVe       = 2 * m_KF.sigmaVe  * m_KF.sigmaVe  * betaVe;  // The process noise value for easting  velocity.
02460     const double qVup      = 2 * m_KF.sigmaVup * m_KF.sigmaVup * betaVup; // The process noise value for up       velocity.
02461     const double qClkDrift = 2 * m_KF.sigmaClkDrift * m_KF.sigmaClkDrift * betaClkDrift; // The process noise value for clock drift.
02462 
02463     double eVn = 0;
02464     double eVe = 0;
02465     double eVup = 0;
02466     double eClkDrift = 0;
02467     double eVn2 = 0;
02468     double eVe2 = 0;
02469     double eVup2 = 0;
02470     double eClkDrift2 = 0;
02471 
02472     const unsigned int u = 8;
02473 
02474     if( Q.nrows() != u )
02475     {
02476       if( !Q.Resize( u, u ) )
02477       {
02478         return false;
02479       }
02480     }
02481     
02482     
02483     eVn        = exp( -betaVn  * dT );
02484     eVe        = exp( -betaVe  * dT );
02485     eVup       = exp( -betaVup * dT );
02486     eClkDrift  = exp( -betaClkDrift * dT );
02487 
02488     eVn2       = exp( -2.0 * betaVn  * dT );
02489     eVe2       = exp( -2.0 * betaVe  * dT );
02490     eVup2      = exp( -2.0 * betaVup * dT );
02491     eClkDrift2 = exp( -2.0 * betaClkDrift * dT );
02492 
02493     Q[0][0]  = qVn / (betaVn*betaVn);
02494     Q[0][0] *= dT - 2.0*(1.0 - eVn)/(betaVn) + (1.0 - eVn2)/(2.0*betaVn);
02495 
02496     Q[1][1]  = qVe / (betaVe*betaVe);
02497     Q[1][1] *= dT - 2.0*(1.0 - eVe)/(betaVe) + (1.0 - eVe2)/(2.0*betaVe);
02498 
02499     Q[2][2]  = qVn / (betaVup*betaVup);
02500     Q[2][2] *= dT - 2.0*(1.0 - eVup)/(betaVup) + (1.0 - eVup2)/(2.0*betaVup);
02501 
02502     Q[3][3]  = qVn * (1.0 - eVn2) / (2.0*betaVn);
02503     
02504     Q[4][4]  = qVe * (1.0 - eVe2) / (2.0*betaVe);
02505 
02506     Q[5][5]  = qVup * (1.0 - eVup2) / (2.0*betaVup);
02507 
02508     Q[6][6]  = qClkDrift / (betaClkDrift*betaClkDrift);
02509     Q[6][6] *= dT - 2.0*(1.0 - eClkDrift)/(betaClkDrift) + (1.0 - eClkDrift2)/(2.0*betaClkDrift);
02510     
02511     Q[7][7]  = qClkDrift * (1.0 - eClkDrift2) / (2.0*betaClkDrift);
02512 
02513     Q[0][3]  = qVn / betaVn;
02514     Q[0][3] *= (1.0 - eVn)/betaVn - (1.0 - eVn2)/(2.0*betaVn);
02515     Q[3][0]  = Q[0][3];
02516 
02517     Q[1][4]  = qVe / betaVe;
02518     Q[1][4] *= (1.0 - eVe)/betaVe - (1.0 - eVe2)/(2.0*betaVe);
02519     Q[4][1]  = Q[1][4];
02520 
02521     Q[2][5]  = qVup / betaVup;
02522     Q[2][5] *= (1.0 - eVup)/betaVup - (1.0 - eVup2)/(2.0*betaVup);
02523     Q[5][2]  = Q[2][5];
02524 
02525     Q[6][7]  = qClkDrift / betaClkDrift;
02526     Q[6][7] *= (1.0 - eClkDrift)/betaClkDrift - (1.0 - eClkDrift2)/(2.0*betaClkDrift);
02527     Q[7][6]  = Q[6][7];
02528 
02529     return true;
02530   }

02617   bool GNSS_Estimator::PredictAhead_8StatePVGM(
02618     GNSS_RxData &rxData, //!< The receiver data.
02619     const double dT,     //!< The change in time since the last update [s].
02620     Matrix &T,           //!< The transition matrix                                 [8 x 8] (output).
02621     Matrix &Q,           //!< The process noise matrix                              [8 x 8] (output).
02622     Matrix &P            //!< The state variance covariance matrix                  [8 x 8] (input/output).      
02623     )
02624   {
02625     double M = 0; // The meridian radius of curvature.
02626     double N = 0; // The prime vertical radius of curvature.
02627     bool result = false;
02628     Matrix tmpMat;
02629     double lat = 0;
02630     double h = 0;
02631 
02632     GEODESY_ComputeMeridianRadiusOfCurvature(
02633       GEODESY_REFERENCE_ELLIPSE_WGS84,
02634       rxData.m_pvt.latitude,
02635       &M );
02636 
02637     GEODESY_ComputePrimeVerticalRadiusOfCurvature(
02638       GEODESY_REFERENCE_ELLIPSE_WGS84,
02639       rxData.m_pvt.latitude,
02640       &N );
02641 
02642     // Get the transition Matrix
02643     result = ComputeTransitionMatrix_8StatePVGM( dT, T );
02644     if( result == false )
02645       return false;
02646 
02647     // Set the process noise Matrix
02648     result = ComputeProcessNoiseMatrix_8StatePVGM( dT, Q );      
02649     if( result == false )
02650       return false;
02651 
02652     
02653     ////
02654     // predict the states ahead    
02655     
02656     // for use of use
02657     lat = rxData.m_pvt.latitude;
02658     h   = rxData.m_pvt.height;
02659     
02660     rxData.m_pvt.latitude  += T[0][3] * rxData.m_pvt.vn / (M+h);  // for small dT, this should be: lat += dT * vn / M
02661     rxData.m_pvt.longitude += T[1][4] * rxData.m_pvt.ve / ((N+h)*cos(lat));  // for small dT, this should be: lon += dT * ve / ((N+h)*cos(lat))
02662     rxData.m_pvt.height    += T[2][5] * rxData.m_pvt.vup;  // for small dT, this should be: hgt += dT * vup    
02663     
02664     rxData.m_pvt.vn  *= T[3][3];  // for small dT, this should be vn = vn    
02665     rxData.m_pvt.ve  *= T[4][4];  // for small dT, this should be ve = ve
02666     rxData.m_pvt.vup *= T[5][5];  // for small dT, this should be vup = vup
02667 
02668     rxData.m_pvt.clockOffset += T[6][7] * rxData.m_pvt.clockDrift;  // for small dT, this should be: clk += dT * clkrate
02669     rxData.m_pvt.clockDrift  *= T[7][7];  // for small dT, this should be clkdrift = clkdrift
02670 
02671     //
02672     ////
02673 
02674 
02675     ////
02676     // predict the new state variance/covariance
02677 
02678     // It can be done this way:
02679     // P = T * P * T.transpose() + Q;
02680     // but the following is more efficient
02681     tmpMat = T;
02682     if( !tmpMat.Inplace_Transpose() )
02683       return false;
02684 
02685     if( !P.Inplace_PreMultiply( T ) )
02686       return false;
02687 
02688     if( !P.Inplace_PostMultiply( tmpMat ) )
02689       return false;
02690 
02691     if( !P.Inplace_Add( Q ) )
02692       return false;
02693     //
02694     ////
02695 
02696     return true;    
02697   }

02817   bool GNSS_Estimator::InitializeStateVarianceCovariance_8StatePVGM(
02818     const double std_lat,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the latitude [m].
02819     const double std_lon,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the longitude [m]. 
02820     const double std_hgt,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the height [m].
02821     const double std_vn,         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the northing velocity [m/s].
02822     const double std_ve,         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the easting velocity [m/s].
02823     const double std_vup,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the up velocity [m/s].
02824     const double std_clk,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the clock offset [m].
02825     const double std_clkdrift,   //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the clock drift [m/s].    
02826     Matrix &P                    //!< The variance covariance of the states [8x8].
02827     )

03208      vup       += dx[5];
03209      clkdrift  += dx[7];

03217        sqrt(P[4][4]),

03573     double dlon = (N + hgt) * cos(lat);

03577     // For each measurement
03578     for( index = 0; index < n; index++ )
03579     {
03580       Matrix h(1,u);  // The i'th row of the design matrix, [ux1].
03581       Matrix ht(u,1); // The transpose of the i'th row of the design matrix, [ux1].
03582       Matrix pht;     // pht = P ht, [ux1].
03583       Matrix C;       // C = (h P ht + R_{ii}), [1x1].

03587       // Copy out a row of the design matrix.

03589       {
03590         h[0][j] = H[index][j];
03591         ht[j][0] = H[index][j];
03592       }
03593       //PrintMatToDebug( "h", h );
03594 
03595       // Compute pht
03596       pht = P;
03597       if( !pht.Inplace_PostMultiply( ht ) )
03598         return false;
03599       
03600       // Compute C = (h P h^T + R_{ii})
03601       C = h * pht;
03602       C[0] += R[index][index];
03603       
03604       // Compute k_i
03605       k_i = pht / C[0];
03606 
03607       //PrintMatToDebug( "k_i", k_i );
03608 
03609       // Update the state variance-coveriance;
03610       D = k_i;
03611       if( !D.Inplace_PostMultiply( h ) )
03612         return false;
03613       if( !D.Inplace_PostMultiply( P ) )
03614         return false;
03615       P -= D;
03616 
03617       
03618       double innovation = w[index];
03619       k_i.Inplace_MultiplyScalar( innovation );
03620       dx = k_i;
03621       //PrintMatToDebug( "dx", dx );
03622 
03623       // Update the position and clock states
03624       // Update height first as it is need to reduce the corrections for lat and lon.
03625       hgt += dx[2];
03626       clk += dx[6];
03627 
03628       // The corrections for lat and lon, dx_p, must be converted to [rad] from [m].
03629       lat += dx[0] / dlat;  // convert from meters to radians.
03630       lon += dx[1] / dlon;  // convert from meters to radians.
03631 
03632       result = rxData->UpdatePositionAndRxClock(
03633         lat,
03634         lon,
03635         hgt,
03636         clk,
03637         sqrt(P[0][0]),
03638         sqrt(P[1][1]),
03639         sqrt(P[2][2]),
03640         sqrt(P[6][6])
03641         );
03642       if( !result )
03643       {
03644         return false;
03645       }
03646 
03647       // Update the velocity and clock drift states.
03648       vn        += dx[3];
03649       ve        += dx[4];
03650       vup       += dx[5];
03651       clkdrift  += dx[7];
03652 
03653       result = rxData->UpdateVelocityAndClockDrift(
03654         vn,
03655         ve,
03656         vup,
03657         clkdrift,
03658         sqrt(P[3][3]),
03659         sqrt(P[4][4]),
03660         sqrt(P[5][5]),
03661         sqrt(P[7][7]) );
03662       if( !result )
03663       {
03664         return false;
03665       }
03666 
03667       result = DeterminePseudorangeMisclosures_GPSL1(
03668         rxData,
03669         rxBaseData,
03670         nrP,
03671         w_p );
03672       if( !result )
03673       {
03674         return false;
03675       }
03676 
03677       result = DetermineDopplerMisclosures_GPSL1(
03678         rxData,
03679         rxBaseData,
03680         nrD,
03681         w_v );
03682       if( !result )
03683       {
03684         return false;
03685       }
03686 
03687       for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
03688       {
03689         if( i < nrP )
03690         {
03691           w[i] = w_p[i];
03692         }
03693         else
03694         {
03695           w[i] = w_v[i-nrP];
03696         }
03697       }            
03698     }
03699     return true;

04289 
04290   bool GNSS_Estimator::DetermineAmbiguitiesChanges( 
04291     GNSS_RxData *rxData,     //!< The receiver data.
04292     GNSS_RxData *rxBaseData, //!< The reference receiver data if any (NULL if not available).
04293     Matrix &P,               //!< The state variance-covariance matrix.
04294     bool& changeOccured 
04295     )
04296   {
04297     unsigned i = 0;
04298     unsigned j = 0;
04299     // First look for ambiguities that are no longer active.
04300     bool isAmbiguityActive = false;      
04301     std::list<stAmbiguityInfo>::iterator iter;
04302     std::list<stAmbiguityInfo>::iterator check_iter;
04303     std::list<stAmbiguityInfo>::iterator remove_iter;
04304     std::list<unsigned int> remove_list;
04305     std::list<unsigned int>::const_iterator list_iter;
04306 
04307     changeOccured = false;
04308 
04309     // At this point the active ambiguities are those that were included in the 
04310     // estimation of the previous epoch. This will change if some of those ambiguites
04311     // are no longer included in the observations.
04312     for( iter = m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.begin(); iter != m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.end();  )
04313     {
04314       isAmbiguityActive = false;
04315       
04316       // For the active ambiguity (iter), search through the observation array to see
04317       // if the ambiguity is still present and if it is to be estimated.      
04318       for( i = 0; i < rxData->m_nrValidObs; i++ )
04319       {
04320         if( // iter->channel == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].channel && // GDM - NO CHANNEL MATCHING FOR RINEX DATA!
04321           iter->id        == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].id &&
04322           iter->system    == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system && 
04323           iter->freqType  == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType &&
04324           rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrUsedInSolution &&
04325           rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialAdrAvailable )
04326         {
04327           // This ambiguity is already actively estimated.
04328           isAmbiguityActive = true;
04329           break;
04330         }
04331       }
04332 
04333       if( !isAmbiguityActive )
04334       {
04335         changeOccured = true;
04336 
04337         // Add the state_index to the list of indices to be
04338         // removed from state variance covariance matrix.        
04339         remove_list.push_back( iter->state_index );
04340 
04341         remove_iter = iter;
04342         ++iter;
04343         m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.erase( remove_iter );        
04344       }
04345       else
04346       {
04347         ++iter;
04348       }
04349     }
04350 
04351     // Deal with removing ambiguities from P.
04352     if( remove_list.size() > 0 )
04353     {
04354       unsigned int *rows = NULL;    
04355       unsigned int nrows = static_cast<unsigned int>(remove_list.size());
04356       rows = new unsigned int[nrows];
04357       if( rows == NULL )
04358       {
04359         return false;
04360       }
04361 
04362       i = 0;
04363       for( list_iter = remove_list.begin(); list_iter != remove_list.end(); ++list_iter )
04364       {
04365         rows[i] = *list_iter;
04366         i++;
04367       }
04368 
04369       //P.Print( "P.now.txt", 10 );
04370       if( !P.RemoveRowsAndColumns( nrows, rows, nrows, rows ) )
04371       {
04372         return false;
04373       }
04374       //P.Print( "P.after.txt", 10 );
04375 
04376       delete [] rows;      
04377     }
04378 
04379       // The indices of the ambiguities in the list are now incorrect due to the removals and must be corrected.
04380       // Update the ambiguities list first, then the state indices contained in rxData->m_ObsArray
04381       for( iter = m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.begin(); iter != m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.end(); ++iter )
04382       {
04383         for( list_iter = remove_list.begin(); list_iter != remove_list.end(); ++list_iter )
04384         {
04385           if( iter->state_index > (int)(*list_iter) )
04386           {
04387             iter->state_index -= 1;
04388           }
04389         }
04390         // Update the observation array with the new info.
04391         for( i = 0; i < rxData->m_nrValidObs; i++ )
04392         {
04393           if( // iter->channel == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].channel  && // GDM - NO CHANNEL MATCHING FOR RINEX DATA!
04394             iter->id        == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].id       &&
04395             iter->system    == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system   && 
04396             iter->freqType  == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType &&
04397             rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrUsedInSolution   &&
04398             rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialAdrAvailable )
04399           {
04400             rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_ambiguity_state = iter->state_index;
04401             break;
04402           }
04403         }      
04404       }
04405       remove_list.clear();
04406     
04407 
04408 
04409     // Add new ambiguities if any.
04410     for( i = 0; i < rxData->m_nrValidObs; i++ )
04411     {
04412       isAmbiguityActive = false;
04413       if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system == GNSS_GPS && rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType == GNSS_GPSL1 )
04414       {
04415         if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isActive )
04416         {
04417           if( rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrUsedInSolution )
04418           {
04419             // Look for this ambiguity in the ambiguities list.
04420             for( iter = m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.begin(); iter != m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.end(); ++iter )
04421             {
04422               if( // iter->channel == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].channel && // GDM - NO CHANNEL MATCHING FOR RINEX DATA!
04423                 iter->id        == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].id      &&
04424                 iter->system    == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system  && 
04425                 iter->freqType  == rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType &&
04426                 rxData->m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialAdrAvailable )
04427               {
04428                 // This ambiguity is already actively estimated.
04429                 isAmbiguityActive = true;
04430                 break;
04431               }
04432             } 
04433 
04434             if( !isAmbiguityActive )
04435             {              
04436               changeOccured = true;
04437 
04438               // Update the active amibguities list.
04439               stAmbiguityInfo amb_info;
04440 
04441               amb_info.channel     = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].channel;
04442               amb_info.id          = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].id;
04443               amb_info.system      = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].system;
04444               amb_info.freqType    = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].freqType;
04445               amb_info.state_index = P.nrows(); // This will be the index of the row and column in P for this ambiguity.
04446 
04447               rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_ambiguity_state = amb_info.state_index;
04448               
04449               m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.push_back( amb_info );
04450 
04451               // Add a new row and columgn to the state variance-covariance matrix.
04452               if( !P.Redim( P.nrows()+1, P.ncols()+1 ) )
04453                 return false;
04454 
04455               // Set the initial variance of the ambiguity state [m].
04456               P[amb_info.state_index][amb_info.state_index] = 125; // KO Arbitrary value, to improve
04457 
04458               // Initialize the ambiguity state [m].
04459               // Compute the single difference adr measurement [m].
04460               double sd_adr_measured = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].adr - rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_differential].adr;
04461               sd_adr_measured *= GPS_WAVELENGTHL1;
04462 
04463               // Compute the single difference psr measurement.
04464               double sd_psr_measured = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].psr - rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_differential].psr;
04465 
04466               // Initialize the ambiguity to the difference between the single difference adr
04467               // and the single difference pseudorange.
04468 
04469               rxData->m_ObsArray[i].ambiguity =  sd_adr_measured - sd_psr_measured; // in meters!  //KO possibly replace psr with position derived range plus clock offset
04470 
04471               //double sd_computed = rxData->m_ObsArray[i].range - rxBaseData->m_ObsArray[rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_differential_adr].range;
04472               //sd_computed += rxData->m_pvt.clockOffset;
04473               //rxData->m_ObsArray[i].ambiguity =  sd_adr_measured - sd_computed;
04474             }
04475           }
04476           else
04477           {
04478             rxData->m_ObsArray[i].index_ambiguity_state = -1;
04479             rxData->m_ObsArray[i].ambiguity = 0.0;
04480           }
04481         }
04482       }
04483     }
04484 
04485     // Check for errors.
04486     i = 0;
04487     j = 0;
04488     for( iter = m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.begin(); iter != m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.end(); ++iter )
04489     {
04490       j=0;
04491       for( check_iter = m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.begin(); check_iter != m_ActiveAmbiguitiesList.end(); ++check_iter )
04492       {
04493         if( i != j )
04494         {
04495           if( check_iter->state_index == iter->state_index )
04496             return false;
04497         }
04498         j++;
04499       }
04500       i++;      
04501     }
04502     
04503 
04504     return true;
04505   }
